ues]\n* [https://www.pbs.org/wgbh/amex/rfk/index.html ''American Experience'': RFK], [[Public Broadcasting Service|PBS]]\n* [http://www.americanrhetoric.com/speeches/rfkonmlkdeath.html Text, Audio, and Video of Robert Kennedy's Remarks on the Assassination of Martin Luther King Jr.]\n* \n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20061003184041/http://www.jfklibrary.org/Historical%2BResources/Archives/Reference%2BDesk/Speeches/EMK/Tribute%2Bto%2BSenator%2BRobert%2BF.%2BKennedy.htm Edward Kennedy eulogy to Robert Kennedy (text and audio)]\n* [https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2009/04/22/AR2009042203088_pf.html My Father's Stand on Cuba Travel] by Kathleen Kennedy Townsend, ''The Washington Post'', April 23, 2009\n* [http://radiotapes.com/specialpostings.html Radio airchecks/recordings] of the shooting and death of Senator Kennedy including Mutual Radio's Andrew West's shooting coverage, continued live coverage from CBS Radio, announcements of RFK's death, CBS Radio's complete coverage of funeral mass St. Patrick's Cathedral, and CBS Radio coverage of the train arrival of RFK's body in Washington DC.\n* [http://www.fuzzymemories.tv/index.php?m=KTTV%20Channel%2011%20-%20Robert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Assassination%20Coverage KTTV assassination coverage] at [[The Museum of Classic Chicago Television]]\n* [http://vault.fbi.gov/Robert%20F%20Kennedy%20%28Assassination%29%20 FBI file on the RFK assassination]\n* [http://www.lib.umassd.edu/archives/swain/rfk-assassination-archives \"The Robert F. Kennedy Assassination Archives\"] \u2013 a collection within the [[University of Massachusetts Dartmouth#Claire T. Carney Library|University of Massachusetts Dartmouth]] Archives and Special Collections established in 1984\n* {{Britannica|314866}} access date February 19, 2019\n* {{C-SPAN|robertkennedy}}\n{{wikilivres}}\n\n{{Robert F. Kennedy}}\n{{Navboxes\n|list1=\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-legal}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[William P. Rogers]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Attorney General]]|years=1961\u20131964}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Nicholas Katzenbach]]}}\n\n{{s-ppo}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Frank Hogan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] nominee for [[United States Senator|U.S. Senator]] from [[New York (state)|New York]]<br />([[Classes of United States Senators|Class 1]])|years=[[United States Senate election in New York, 1964|1964]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Richard Ottinger]]}}\n\n{{s-par|us-sen}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Kenneth Keating]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[List of United States Senators from New York|U.S. Senator (Class 1) from New York]]|years=1965\u20131968|alongside=[[Jacob K. Javits]]}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Charles Goodell]]}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{USAttGen}}\n{{United States Senators from New York}}\n{{Kennedy family}}\n{{John F. Kennedy}}\n{{Ted Kennedy}}\n{{Kennedy cabinet}}\n{{LBJohnson cabinet}}\n{{1964 United States presidential election}}\n{{1968 United States presidential election}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Civil rights movement|Law|United States|Politics}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kennedy, Robert F.}}\n[[Category:Robert F. Kennedy| ]]\n[[Category:1925 births]]\n[[Category:1968 deaths]]\n[[Category:1968 murders in the United States]]\n[[Category:20th-century American writers]]\n[[Category:20th-century American politicians]]\n[[Category:American anti-communists]]\n[[Category:American naval personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:American murder victims]]\n[[Category:Anti-poverty advocates]]\n[[Category:Assassinated American politicians]]\n[[Category:Bates College people]]\n[[Category:Burials at Arlington National Cemetery]]\n[[Category:Catholics from Massachusetts]]\n[[Category:Civil rights movement]]\n[[Category:Congressional Gold Medal recipients]]\n[[Category:People murdered in California]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in California]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party United States senators]]\n[[Category:Harvard Crimson football players]]\n[[Category:Harvard College alumni]]\n[[Category:International opponents of aparthe