entative, New Orleans City Council member, state circuit judge from 1982 to 1998<ref>{{cite news|url=http://obits.nola.com/obituaries/nola/obituary.aspx?n=philip-charles-ciaccio&pid=176486531&fhid=5630|title=Philip Charles Ciaccio|newspaper=[[New Orleans Times-Picayune]]|accessdate=November 14, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[John Elton Coon]], state representative from [[Ouachita Parish, Louisiana|Ouachita Parish]]; the mayor of [[Monroe, Louisiana|Monroe]] from 1949 to 1956, and state fire marshal from 1956 to 1964 (D)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-yearbook.com/yearbooks/Tulane_University_Jambalaya_Yearbook/1929/Page_149.html|title=Tulane University, Freshman Class of 1929, p. 149|publisher=e-yearbook.com|accessdate=July 8, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Eddie Doucet]], former state representative for Jefferson Parish<ref>\"Louisiana: Doucet, Eddie A.\", ''Who's Who in American Politics, 2003-2004'', 19th ed., Vol. 1 (Alabama-Montana) (Marquis Who's Who: [[New Providence, New Jersey|New Providence]], [[New Jersey]], 2003), p. 777</ref> \n* [[Frank Fulco]], state representative from Shreveport; leader of Italian American community in Louisiana (D)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.e-yearbook.com/yearbooks/Tulane_University_Jambalaya_Yearbook/1929/Page_149.html|title=Tulane University, Freshman Class of 1929, p. 149|publisher=e-yearbook.com|accessdate=July 8, 2013}}</ref>\n* [[Cameron Henry]], member of Louisiana House (R){{Citation needed|date=January 2013}}\n* [[Nita Hutter|Nita Rusich Hutter]], M. Ed. 1978, state representative from St. Bernard Parish (R)<ref>{{cite web|title=Nita Hutter|url=http://votesmart.org/candidate/biography/54284/nita-hutter#.UQHTdidZWBE|publisher=Project Vote Smart|accessdate=25 January 2013}}</ref> \n* [[Adam Kwasman]], B.A. Economics 2003, member of Arizona House of Representatives District 11; 2014 candidate for U.S. Congress (R)\n* [[Elwyn Nicholson]], state senator from Jefferson Parish from 1972 to 1988 (D)<ref>{{cite news|url=http://blog.nola.com/nola_daily_obits_newsletter/2014/10/former_sen_elwyn_nicholson_wes.html|title=Sen. Elwyn Nicholson, a West Bank grocer, Jean Lafitte National Park proponent, dies at 90|author=Andrea Shawdate=October 10, 2014|newspaper=[[New Orleans Times-Picayune]]|accessdate=October 17, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141023004810/http://blog.nola.com/nola_daily_obits_newsletter/2014/10/former_sen_elwyn_nicholson_wes.html|archive-date=October 23, 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n* [[Karen Carter Peterson]], state representative and candidate for United States House of Representatives from Louisiana (D)\n* [[Weldon Russell]], state representative from Tangipahoa and St. Helena parishes from 1984 to 1988; Realtor in [[Amite City, Louisiana|Amite]] (D)\n* [[Jock Scott]], former state representative from Alexandria (D)-turned-(R)\n* [[Scott Simon (politician)|Scott M. Simon]], architect and state representative (R)\n* [[Paul Spitzfaden]], B.A. 1957, mayor of Mandeville, 1984-1996 (R)<ref>\"Louisiana: Spitzfaden, Paul Riley, ''Who's Who in American Politics, 2003-2004'', 19th ed., Vol. 1 (Alabama-Montana) (Marquis Who's Who: [[New Providence, New Jersey|New Providence]], [[New Jersey]], 2003), p. 795</ref> \n* [[Roy R. Theriot]], Law, former Louisiana comptroller, 1960-1973 (D)\n* [[Tom Thornhill]], postgraduate study, [[Slidell, Louisiana|Slidell]] attorney and member of the Louisiana House of Representatives from 1996-2000 (R)<ref>\"House District 76\", ''Louisiana Encyclopedia'' (1999)</ref>\n* [[Joseph F. Toomy]], B.A. and M.B.A., former state representative from Jefferson Parish (R)<ref>\"House District 85\", ''Louisiana Encyclopedia'' (1999)</ref>\n* [[Chris Ullo]], member of both houses of the Louisiana legislature from 1972 to 2008 (D)\n* [[Eric Skrmetta]], an attorney from Metairie, Louisiana, who is a Republican member of the Louisiana Public Service Commission for District 1. (R)\n\n====Other====\n* [[Tom Capella]], '87, assessor of Jefferson Parish; former state representa